    "in [172] examined gradient inversion attacks and defense mechanisms.",
    "introduced CAFE in [173], a method to recover large batch data from gradients.",
    "proposed FL-WBC in [174], a defense mechanism against global model poisoning.",
    "Fed-Defender [175] also focuses on the client side to achieve attack tolerance, which consists of local meta update and global distillation.",
    "Park et al."
